parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the automatic seat belt buckle can increase the risk of injury or death in the event of an accident, as the occupant may not be properly restrained.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is inoperative
the seat belt buckle fails to latch or unlatch
the seat belt buckle is stuck
the lap-shoulder belt stops halfway in the track.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake caliper sticking in the closed position can cause premature wear of the brake pads, leading to inadequate brake performance and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: Premature wear of brake pads
brake pads wearing excessively
brake pedal going to the floor
inadequate brake action in normal stop and go conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The loss of hydraulic brakes can cause complete brake failure, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Total loss of hydraulic brakes
brake pedal going to the floor
inadequate brake action in normal stop and go conditions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the brake rotor from the hub can cause loss of brake performance and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Brake rotor separation from the hub
brake malfunction
excessive brake pad wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS brake system can cause complete brake loss, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: ABS brake system malfunction
complete brake loss
premature wear of brake pads.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The repeated failure of brake components, such as disc brakes, rotors, and master cylinders, can cause frequent brake malfunctions and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Frequent brake component failure
repeated replacement of brake components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden failure of the clutch cable can cause the loss of clutch function, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch cable breaks
leaving the vehicle without a clutch to shift gears
especially at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the floor mount shift can cause the transmission to slip out of gear, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The floor mount shift becomes shaky
the transmission slips out of gear
the vehicle may jerk or hesitate while shifting.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unexpected sudden acceleration can cause the vehicle to accelerate rapidly, leading to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates suddenly when shifting into reverse
the vehicle may lurch or jerk forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Rotor Separation and Transmission Problems
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The separation of the brake rotor from the hub can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, and transmission problems can lead to loss of control and potential accidents.
symptoms: The brake rotor separates from the hub
the timing belt breaks
transmission problems occur
such as slipping or hesitation.
